  "title": "Planning Engineer (Changi)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Assists in the tender process by planning work execution sequences and proposing value engineering solutions.</li>\n  <li>Develops the master program for the project using Excel or MS Project.</li>\n  <li>Prepares the Project Quality Plan and ensures its effective implementation on site.</li>\n  <li>Ensures all works are carried out in accordance with the Project Quality Plan; monitors and inspects materials and equipment to confirm they meet approved quality standards.</li>\n  <li>Prepares Method Statements and collaborates with the Safety Team to conduct risk assessments in compliance with Authority requirements.</li>\n  <li>Coordinates with relevant Authorities and submits necessary applications to meet all statutory requirements.</li>\n  <li>Conducts site inspections and internal audits to ensure work quality aligns with project standards and building codes.</li>\n  <li>Maintains an organized documentation system to ensure traceability of data and records.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Preferable 10 years of relevant experience in the Construction industry</li>\n  <li>Diploma or Bachelor’s Degree in Civil Engineering/ Construction management or equivalent</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>\n<p>EA Personnel No: R22110981</p>\n<p>EA Personnel Name: Law Mei Fong</p>",
